<br>
::He did not know if Persephone was being sarcastic with her first comment, but he was used to being teased, so he shrugged it off. He started wading to the shoreline, as the water got lower and lower on him, his limp became apparent. He had no shame of his body, therefore did not bother covering up as he approached the chair beside Persephone. He took the towel from that chair and dried himself off. He then wrapped the towel around his waist, then running his hands through his hair and his beard, trying to keep them from knotting up. He then picked up the honeysuckle pie and sat down in the chair beside her, then of course producing his own goblet::<br>
<br>
::Hephaestus then cordially smiled to Persephone in thanks, and spoke up laughingly:: &quot;Actually, I'd be more afraid to find Hades reaction FOR sitting next to you.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He then took a deep sigh and a small bite from the pie:: &quot;Mmmm...as usual, superb. So anyway, you recently returned from Tartarus, didn't you? Anything new down there?&quot;<br>
<br>
::He then stretched a little bit before taking another bite and a sip from his wine goblet:: &quot;I've been meaning to go down there...check up on the chains that hold the Titans' Door closed, make sure they are still secure. Also, I need to lobby Hades for some fresh gems and jewels, I'm running low and have some ideas for jewlery and weapons that need them. I finally got ahead on work, so I'm taking some time off. Relaxing.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He said with a smile. He forgets himself sometimes, as he rarely has anyone to talk to, once he gets started, he sometimes rambles on and on:: &quot;So, any suprises this Spring for us?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=persephoneqofu>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 174<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/11/03 10:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=308.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.aishwarya-rai.com/tradi/tash16.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Work-a-holic</span><hr size=1> ::Persephone looked at Hephaestus as he walked out of the water. As he walks over to her with his masculine 'definition' in the open, she turns her head away, covering her eyes with her hands while showing an innocent blush with an adorable giggle. Even though she had been to bed with Hades, it still made her bashful to see a man's possesions. Looking at him as he sat down, she listens to him with genuine interest as he rambles on and on animatedly. She knew that he did not get a chance to do that much, especially with their type of peers around. Upon hearing his comment on Hades, she breaks out in fun laughter::<br>
<br>
Perhaps, but then again, so many people are afraid of Hades. Although he can be terrifying when he wants to be, he is pretty calm and mellow most of the time. Do you know that most mortals fear to even say his name openly and in vain, even more so than Zeus himself. To anwser your next question, I can't really say that anything is new in Tartarus. Same old cold, boring,scary atmostsphere. I keep telling Hades that we should move our palace to the Elysian Fields where its much more beautiful, but he insists that he has to keep a close eye on the souls that are damned. You'd think that was that darned three-headed dog's job. You know he almost bit my head off when I tried to run away the first time. I would have escaped if he hadn't seen my aura.<br>
<br>
::Taking a sip, She looks out at the lush ocean and the sea birds flying in the salty breeze:: Now that you mention the chains, they are a bit rusty. Last eon, a soul tried to open them up and the Titans almost escaped. Thank goodness a few of the other gods were down there, it could have been chaos. <br>
<br>
::Upon hearing his request for stones, Persephone laughs plentifully:: Oh Hephaestus, you know perfectly well that you many take as many stones as you like. We always have more than we'd like to handle. And speaking of weapons, do you think you could make great sword with black diamonds encrusted on a hilt made of silver? I think it would be a wonderful gift for Hades! If it isn't too much trouble to do, I'd greatly appreciate it.<br>
<br>
::Putting her empty plate aside, she wipes her lips daintily with a soft little hanky:: I don't really have any new plans for this spring. I'll help my mother around as usual. If anything, I'm looking forward to Hades visiting me when my mother isn't home. Its hard but I think we can work around it. My mother's demi-god friends are thinking of throwing a welcome home gala in my honor, but I asked them not to because I don't think anyone would really come. And wouldn't that make me look stupid.. <br>
<br>
::Taking a sip of wine, she stops sipping abruptly, putting her glass down. Many goddesses were now afraid to be around Hephaestus after the rape of Athena, but Persephone wasn't scared. She knew Hephaestus cared about her too much to do that. Not to mention the wrath of Hades and Demeter against him would be unstoppable. Turning towards him, she speaks to Hephaestus in a gentle voice and her eyes full of understanding. :: Hephaestus, I want to ask you a question. Remember how to came to Athena and, well....you know. What made you want to do it, I mean, it just seemed so strange. Like it wasn't even you.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
