<br>
::The smile left Hephaestus' face as he sighed deeply, then took a deep drink from his goblet of wine, finishing off whatever was in there::<br>
<br>
::He muttered:: &quot;I'm probably the laughing stock of Olympus because of it, and those who do not laugh are probably afraid.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He then looked at Persephone, straight in the eyes:: &quot;What possessed me to do such an act?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Truth be known, I have desired Athena for quite some time...&quot; ::He smiled slightly and seemed to stare off into space as he spoke:: &quot;Almost literally since I helped 'birth' her, by opening up Zeus's head to aleviate his headache and thus freeing her.&quot;<br>
<br>
::The smile left his face almost as quickly as it came:: &quot;Apparently, Poseidon wanted revenge on Athena for some rivalry they have. So, Poseidon played upon my deepest heart's desire, and told me that Athena had mutual feelings for me, that she felt the same about me that I felt about her. I should have known better; known that it was too good to be true...but I wanted to believe it with my whole heart. She came to my forge in Mt. Aetna. My desires overtook my reason and I attacked her. I guess part of me felt, that Zeus, Apollo, Aries and countless other gods, take whatever or whomever they want, regardless of whether they are wanted in return. I guess and inkling within me felt the same liberty, especially convinced that she DID want me.&quot; ::He looked right at Persephone:: &quot;Even Hades...went and took what he desired without asking.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;But the difference is, that I failed. Also, I think I'm experiences that none of the other gods feel after being successful at such an act. Remorse. Guilt. Which is why I disappeared to my forge. To lose myself in my work again. I worked for months nonstop until my muscles could not take anymore, so now...I am here, trying to relax, trying to find new ways to forget myself.&quot;<br>
<br>
::With that, he poured himself another goblet of wine. He sipped and contiued looking at Persephone, awaiting her reaction:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=persephoneqofu>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 175<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/12/03 5:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=308.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.aishwarya-rai.com/tradi/tash16.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Inevitable Question...</span><hr size=1> ::Persephone looks at him while nodding and adding a few &quot;umhmms&quot; every once in a while. After he finishes, she sighs and takes his big hands into her small petite ones.::<br>
<br>
Poseidon should be damned for what he did to you. I can understand why you did what you did. In a way, it wasn't your fault seeing as how you thought she actually cared for you and that taking what you wanted is a prevalent gene with the males in our family. As far as Hades goes, considering the fact that he asked my father for my hand in marriage, that qualified him as asking before taking.  ::Smiling faintly, she shakes her head:: But to this day, even with my dear Hades, it feels like he took what he wanted without permission. Although the thing about him raping me was a very weird rumor. Aside from kidnapping me,he never touched me. <br>
<br>
::looking at Hephaestus with her light golden eyes full of compassion:: but the main thing is that you felt guilt. Which is something that almost all the gods do not have the dignity to feel after doing such a violating thing let alone attempting to do it. ::Leaning over, she kisses him gently on the lips and smiles lovingly:: and that is what makes you so much greater than all the rest.. <p>*~* Persephone...Queen of the Underworld.. Faithful wife to Hades... Princess Goddess of the Spring*~*</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=persephoneqofu>PersephoneQofU</A> at: 4/12/03 5:16:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ixhephaestusxi>IX Hephaestus XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/12/03 11:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=308.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Inevitable Question...</span><hr size=1> ::Hephaestus couldn't help but smile at Persephone's last comment. He kiss upon his lips definitly brightened the smile::<br>
